snippet.title: Coke Studio Bharat | Khalasi | Aditya Gadhvi x Achint
snippet.description:
#Khalasi tells the tale of the limitless sailor who has set out to explore through the shores of Gujarat. The song speaks of his tenuous, adventurous voyage, his delightful experiences and his enthusiasm with which he takes on life while he is sailing away!

Headlining the song is iconic music composer Achint Thakkar whose musical landscape tends to be inspired by the 70’s and aims to draw a narrative through his musical notes.  

He is joined by famous playback singer from Gujarat, Aditya Gadhvi. Known for singing in several languages and producing numerous chart hits that were singles. 

In addition to them, the song also boasts of Dhruv Visvanath, India’s premier solo percussive acoustic guitarist who also happens to be a professional singer-songwriter, and producer.  
Join them on this musical voyage.

Follow us on Instagram: Http://www.instagram.com/CokeStudioBharat

snippet.title: Coke Studio Bharat | Geejaga Hakki | Sanjith Hegde x Charan Raj
snippet.description:
In a world where deception and false narratives are pervasive, speaking the truth takes immense courage as it holds so much power. Raja Harishchandra, who appears in various texts and folklore as the epitome of truth, was a legendary king known for his unwavering commitment towards truth and justice, even when society opposed him. #GeejagaHakki portrays life in a world driven by dishonesty and fake news, where choosing the right path means standing against everyone. With Sanjith Hegde, Gen Z's beloved playback singer from the Kannada industry, lending his euphonious voice and Charan Raj as the producer, the song stands out with its unique tunes and dedication showcasing the power of "truth" through music. We also have Prasannakumar Hegde, a popular Yakshagaana artist, bringing the tales of Raja Harishchandra to life.

snippet.title: Coke Studio Bharat | Kya Karie Korimol | ALIF x Noor Mohammad x Aashima Mahajan
snippet.description:
A father-daughter relationship envelopes immense compassion, protection and love. They own a special connection that grows stronger with time and never fades away. #KyaKarieKorimol unveils such a beautiful father-daughter bond on a wedding day. The lyrics narrate the emotional journey of a bride and her father while they prepare for her wedding feast. 

Featuring Alif, a poet, a singer and a songwriter who bagged the IRAA Award for his single ‘Like A Sufi’. Truly recognized as Mohammad Muneem Nazir, his poignant and melancholic lyrical compositions are known for their colloquial references to society.
He’s accompanied by the very soulful Aashima Mahajan who happens to be a very well-known Indian musician, and playback singer, performer, and actor. Having been trained in Indian and Western Classical (Opera), she has given her voice to several celebrated songs.
These esteemed artists were complemented by Noor Mohammad, an Indian traditional Sufi music performer and songwriter, from Baki-Aker village in North Kashmir.
Tune in to this masterpiece, to get a glimpse of a father-daughter love.

snippet.title: Coke Studio Bharat | Taqdeer | Donn Bhat x Rashmeet Kaur x Prabh Deep x Sakur Khan
snippet.description:
Taqdeer as we call it - destiny, is a beautiful connotation that has us enveloped in a myriad of emotions expressed through the conversational poetic rhyme scheme of Bait Baazi reflecting through every powerful verse sung by #RashmeetKaur where we enveloped the #poetry of #Bullehshah and #PrabhDeep ’s soulful spoken word, coming to life with the musical magic of #DonnBhat. Woven through the ethereal poetry are the powerful verses of the #folkmusic of Takdeer Banayo Fakeer sung by #SakurKhanSufi and sons that bring to this magical music the nuances of rooted mangniyaar music. To bring to life the magic of our destiny – #Taqdeer
